    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@vvo \n\n> I have carefully read the test diff but fail to see where we missed the count? Only thing I see is that the datastructure for hierarchical facet was not the same than the others (missing {name, count}).\n\nFor the tests, I wasn't using the same data structure than what the helper was sending.\n\nI was using\n\n``` js\nhierarchicalFacets: [{\n  name: 'hierarchicalFacet1',\n    data: {\n      hierarchicalFacet1val1: 4\n    }\n  }\n}]\n```\n\nWhere in fact, the helper would send back\n\n``` js\nhierarchicalFacets: [{\n  name: 'hierarchicalFacet1',\n    data: {\n      hierarchicalFacet1val1: {name: 'hierarchicalFacet1val1', count: 4}\n    }\n  }\n}]\n```\n\nSo the test worked, but not in real life, where the helper wouldn't actually send data like this.\n\n> > It now only returns the last value\n> \n> Can you precise what do you mean here?\n\nSure : instead of returning \"Cat > Subcat > Subsubcat\", I now only returns \"SubSubCat\". It's ok, since this function is only used for `clearAll` and `currentRefinedValues`.\nThis is to avoid having \"Long Category Name > Long subcategory Name > ...\" in the list.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-11-30T13:43:01Z",
